 "categoryNotes": [
  "Alkalinity is the parameter to test most often \u2014 it drives coral skeletal growth and buffers pH; stability matters more than an exact number.",
  "Digital colorimeters (Hanna) give an objective LED/photocell readout; titration and comparator kits (Salifert, Red Sea) end on a human-judged color \u2014 the single most repeated complaint across owner forums, and a real source of kit-to-kit variance.",
  "ICP lab tests ($30-50, every 3-4 months) cross-check trace elements and validate your kits \u2014 they do not replace weekly alkalinity/nutrient testing.",
  "Salifert's phosphate range is published in phosphorus (PO4-P), not phosphate ion \u2014 multiply by ~3.066 before comparing to Hanna/Red Sea numbers."
 ]
